{
    "analysis": "We have aggregated anomalies across metric, trace, and log data for the incident window (2022-03-20 09:00–09:30 UTC+8). Key findings so far: error_logs are heavily concentrated on frontend pods (frontend-2, frontend-0, frontend-1) starting at 09:00:01+08:00; metric-level anomaly counts are highest for frontend pods but many services and several nodes also show elevated anomaly counts; trace spikes are short (mostly 1–2 points) across multiple services. At this stage we still lack a clear single sustained fault. Per the workflow, the next step is fault identification: convert the per-point anomalies into consecutive anomaly runs (fault candidates), filter out isolated single-point spikes, and rank faults by severity (magnitude of breach relative to global threshold). This will let us (a) find which component-KPIs had sustained deviations during the incident window, (b) obtain each fault's earliest occurrence time (for root-cause occurrence), and (c) measure which faults deviate most from normal (to choose level/component). I will therefore ask the Executor to compute consecutive anomaly runs for metric anomalies inside the incident window and report the top candidates by severity.",
